	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				It may just be the antihistamine that is talking (damn iksar allergies!), but after reading the quest statement the hermit gives you for the 100000129824389 time and along the lines of what someone else said in here it clicked.<BR>
<BR>
The Hermit is a blasphamer and hence a follower of Dag, like Smaaug had said :P. (although he casts no wiz spells)<BR>
<BR>
So that leads us DIRECTLY to the Dalnir forge as per the history of Dag.  Which THEN takes us to the dagger.  The dagger falls into the lines of &quot;what use to be&quot;.  Now if you read the book like I know we all have many times...the dagger was never &quot;finished&quot; and fully enchanted.  This &quot;hilt&quot; is to replace the one from the past hilt in Dalnir used for the dagger.  You must use it along with the other 3 peaces of the dagger plus the undead smith hammer.  Combine and voila you get a nice upgrade to the viseral dagger(that only iksars can use) and what you need to turn in.<BR>
<BR>
The line &quot;With it shall be your Sorcerer's Skullcap&quot; like Smaaug had said once more, does in fact mean turn the new dagger in along with your Sorcerer's Skull Cap (the 7th cap).  The key here is &quot;With IT&quot;...it is the dagger and &quot;shall be&quot; is meant as &quot;along with&quot;.<BR>
<BR>
Turn both in and BHAM our very sweet 8th cap!<BR>
<BR>
At least I hope, I am at work as I write this...just wanted to get  it out before I get home and online and head to dalnir to think &quot;now what am I doing in this greenie dungeon again?&quot;<BR>
<BR>
Smaaug yeah I head read on a ezboard about someone hacking the file and mentioning 9 caps.  But I hope very much that what I just summerized here works out. &lt;crosses his scaly fingers&gt;<BR>
<BR>
Bloodless Soultaker<BR>
41 iksar necro<BR>
Sol Ro
